<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC41CD61FF0C85E752A1FDA4" blockId="56.[189,1399,1965,2025]" lastBlockId="57.[188,1399,263,522]" lastPageId="57" lastPageNumber="58" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
The species of 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC41CD60FECC85E7524CF86A" authorityName="Mey" authorityYear="2004" box="[381,553,1965,1991]" class="Aves" family="Pycnonotidae" genus="Philopteroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC41CD60FECC85E7524CF86A" box="[381,553,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Philopteroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
parasitizing bulbuls appear to form a homogenous group within the 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC41CD60FF0C858451B1F845" box="[189,468,1998,2024]" class="Aves" family="Pycnonotidae" genus="Philopteroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mitsusui">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC41CD60FF0C858451B1F845" box="[189,468,1998,2024]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Philopteroides mitsusui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC41CD60FD648584538EF845" author="Valim M. P. &amp; Palma R. L." box="[725,1003,1998,2024]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="71 - 89" refId="ref37365" refString="Valim M. P. &amp; Palma R. L. 2013. Three new species of the genus Philopteroides Mey, 2004 (Phthiraptera, Ischnocera, Philopteridae) from New Zealand. ZooKeys 297: 71 - 89. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 297.5118" type="journal article" year="2013">Valim &amp; Palma (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. In particular, the species known from bulbuls are united by the following characters: Mesosome covers central ⅓ of distal margin of basal apodeme (
<figureCitation id="F6BE2A6FDC40CD61FECA83655182FEE4" box="[379,487,303,329]" captionStart="Figs 108–111" captionStartId="60.[189,241,1854,1880]" captionTargetBox="[341,1243,592,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-148@60.[341,1247,589,1811]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="Figs 108–111. Philopteroides cucphuongensis Mey, 2004. 108. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 109. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 110. Male genitalia, ventral view. 111. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view. Abbreviations: ads = anterior dorsal seta; dsms = dorsal submarginal seta; mts1–3 = marginal temporal seta 1–3; pos = preocular seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2; s4 = postantennal head sensillum 4." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358766" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358766/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Figs 109</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F6BE2A6FDC40CD61FE4283655247FEE7" box="[499,546,303,330]" captionStart="Figs 114–117" captionStartId="64.[189,241,1925,1951]" captionTargetBox="[349,1238,654,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-117@64.[341,1247,652,1877]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="Figs 114–117. Philopteroides holosternus sp. nov. 114. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 115. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 116. Male genitalia, ventral view. 117. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358770/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">115</figureCitation>
); parameres curved medianly (
<figureCitation id="F6BE2A6FDC40CD61FC3E83655457FEE4" box="[911,1074,303,329]" captionStart="Figs 108–111" captionStartId="60.[189,241,1854,1880]" captionTargetBox="[341,1243,592,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-148@60.[341,1247,589,1811]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="Figs 108–111. Philopteroides cucphuongensis Mey, 2004. 108. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 109. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 110. Male genitalia, ventral view. 111. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view. Abbreviations: ads = anterior dorsal seta; dsms = dorsal submarginal seta; mts1–3 = marginal temporal seta 1–3; pos = preocular seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2; s4 = postantennal head sensillum 4." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358766" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358766/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Figs 109–110</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F6BE2A6FDC40CD61FB8E836554CDFEE7" box="[1087,1192,303,330]" captionStart="Figs 114–117" captionStartId="64.[189,241,1925,1951]" captionTargetBox="[349,1238,654,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-117@64.[341,1247,652,1877]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="Figs 114–117. Philopteroides holosternus sp. nov. 114. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 115. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 116. Male genitalia, ventral view. 117. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358770/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">115–116</figureCitation>
); at least some of sternal plates III–VI reduced in female, with accessory lateral sternal plates (if visible) clearly separated from central sternal plates in at least some segments (
<figureCitation id="F6BE2A6FDC40CD61FC84833653FAFE3B" box="[821,927,380,406]" captionStart="Figs 106–107" captionStartId="59.[189,241,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[345,1245,820,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-126@59.[342,1246,819,1889]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="Figs 106–107. Philopteroides cucphuongensis Mey, 2004. 106. Male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 107. Female habitus, dorsal and ventral views. Abbreviations: ps = paratergal seta; ss = sutural seta; sts = sternal seta; tps = tergal posterior seta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358760" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358760/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Figs 107</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F6BE2A6FDC40CD61FC1D833653BEFE3B" box="[940,987,380,406]" captionStart="Figs 112–113" captionStartId="63.[189,241,1960,1986]" captionTargetBox="[346,1242,929,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-129@63.[346,1242,924,1908]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="Figs 112–113. Philopteroides holosternus sp. nov. 112. Male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 113. Female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358768/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">113</figureCitation>
). In males of most species, at least sternal plate III is reduced in the same way (
<figureCitation id="F6BE2A6FDC40CD61FD0B83E85378FE10" box="[698,797,418,445]" captionStart="Figs 106–107" captionStartId="59.[189,241,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[345,1245,820,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-126@59.[342,1246,819,1889]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="Figs 106–107. Philopteroides cucphuongensis Mey, 2004. 106. Male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 107. Female habitus, dorsal and ventral views. Abbreviations: ps = paratergal seta; ss = sutural seta; sts = sternal seta; tps = tergal posterior seta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358760" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358760/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
), but in 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC40CD61FCC883E85407FE11" authorityName="Mey" authorityYear="2004" box="[889,1122,418,444]" class="Aves" family="Pycnonotidae" genus="Philopteroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cucphoungensis">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC40CD61FCC883E85407FE11" box="[889,1122,418,444]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Ph. cucphoungensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the central sternal plate may be connected to the accessory lateral sternal plates (
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC40CD61FCD483835381FE4E" author="Mey E." box="[869,996,457,483]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="149 - 203" refId="ref36265" refString="Mey E. 2004. Zur Taxonomie, Verbreitung und parasitophyletischer Evidenz des Philopterus - Komplexes (Insecta, Phthiraptera, Ischnocera). Ornithologischer Anzeiger 43: 149 - 203." type="journal article" year="2004">Mey 2004</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 23d), and in 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC40CD61FB0D83835512FE4E" authority="Gustafsson &amp; Najer &amp; Zou &amp; Bush, 2022" authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Najer &amp; Zou &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[1212,1399,457,483]" class="Aves" family="Pycnonotidae" genus="Philopteroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="holosternus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC40CD61FB0D83835512FE4E" box="[1212,1399,457,483]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Ph. holosternus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="47C25783DC40CD61FF0E83BA517FFDA7" box="[191,282,496,522]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
male sternite III is entire (
<figureCitation id="F6BE2A6FDC40CD61FDE083A552D2FDA4" box="[593,695,495,521]" captionStart="Figs 112–113" captionStartId="63.[189,241,1960,1986]" captionTargetBox="[346,1242,929,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-129@63.[346,1242,924,1908]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="Figs 112–113. Philopteroides holosternus sp. nov. 112. Male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 113. Female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358768/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Fig. 112</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
